\C[29][Noah]\C[0] "I see. So you were warned by the sorcerer general Rinny."
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] "Yes. Even Regnus Grahardt said we couldn't beat them."

\C[29][Noah]\C[0] "And here I thought Regnus Grahardt and the Knights of Messiah were our only
hope."
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] "Right. I'm wondering what we should do now."
\C[29][Noah]\C[0] "Why not consult with Lady Rade?"

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] "But Lady Rade... I don't think she'll help us. She has no interest in our
country."
\C[29][Noah]\C[0] "But there's no one else to turn to but Lady Rade. Try asking her again."
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] "Alright. As you say, Noah. I'll consult with Lady Rade."
heroine_2
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] "It's nothing."

\C[29][Noah]\C[0] "Luna, even if we ask the Knights of Messiah for help, we'll need money, right?
Can we really prepare such funds?"
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] "I don't know. But I'll try to find a way."
\C[29][Noah]\C[0] "Don't push yourself too hard, okay? I... I truly love you, Luna..."
\C[29][Noah]\C[0] "Can I hold you...?"
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] "Yes... Noah, I love you."
\C[29][Noah]\C[0] "I love you too, Luna. I really do..."
Luna and Noah held each other for a long time.

Noah pulled Luna close to his body repeatedly, embracing her as if to confirm
their love. Luna embraced Noah in return.

Luna and Noah have been childhood friends who encouraged each other since they
were little. They grew up together in a chaotic world.

Finally united, Luna and Noah's love was bound by a strong tie even in an
unfortunate world.
This night, too, they held each other tightly.
And then Luna and the others headed for Lady Rade's mansion.
